cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper presents algorithms for reducing computation and increasing speed in classifiers used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as part-of-speech tagging, named entity recognition, and dependency parsing. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques for parameter estimation and feature selection, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions experiments involving image processing, which could indicate a connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper's focus on reducing computation and increasing speed could suggest a connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
